# SaaS Design System Rules

Follow `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` for all UI and frontend work in this project.

- Use only the typography, color palette, spacing tokens, components, and layout rules defined in `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`.
- Do not introduce new fonts, colors, spacing values, or border-radius values beyond what the design system defines.
- Use CSS variables (e.g. `var(--color-primary)`, `var(--sp-4)`) instead of hardcoded hex values or arbitrary pixel values.
- Keep navbar, header, footer, buttons, cards, inputs, layout, and animations consistent with the spec.
- If a requested change conflicts with the design system, warn the user and suggest a compliant alternative.

